---
import Legal from '../layouts/Legal.astro';
import { SITE } from '../data/site';
const ENTITY = 'Siterra';
---

<Legal title="Terms of Service" updated="June 12, 2026" path="/terms" description="The terms that govern Siterra's website design and development services, payment, the Design-First Guarantee, ownership, and care plans.">
  <p>
    These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use of {SITE.domain} and the website design and
    development services provided by {ENTITY} ("we", "us"). By purchasing a package or
    using our site, you agree to these Terms.
  </p>

  <h2>Services</h2>
  <p>
    Siterra provides website design, development, copywriting, and related services as described in
    the package you select. Specific deliverables, timelines, and revision rounds are defined by your
    chosen package and any add-ons purchased at checkout. Timelines begin at project kickoff and may
    adjust based on the timeliness of materials and feedback you provide.
  </p>

  <h2>Payment</h2>
  <p>
    Project fees are billed in full at checkout via our payment processor, Stripe. Optional monthly
    care plans are billed as recurring subscriptions. First 30 days included. Monthly billing starts
    after the trial. Cancel before the first monthly charge at no cost. You authorize us and Stripe
    to charge your selected payment method for the amounts shown at checkout.
  </p>

  <h2>The Design-First Guarantee</h2>
  <p>
    We present a design direction for your approval before building out your full site. If the design
    direction is not right for you and we are unable to make it right, you may request a full refund
    of your project fee before full build-out begins. Full details are on our
    <a href="/refunds">Refunds &amp; Guarantee</a> page.
  </p>

  <h2>Client responsibilities</h2>
  <p>
    You agree to provide accurate business information, timely feedback, and any content (text, images,
    logos) you wish to include, and you confirm you have the rights to all materials you supply. Delays
    in providing materials or approvals may affect delivery timelines.
  </p>

  <h2>Ownership</h2>
  <p>
    Upon final payment, you own the website we deliver — including its design, code, and content — along
    with the associated domain and hosting accounts set up in your name. Siterra retains the right to
    display the completed work in our portfolio unless you request otherwise in writing.
  </p>

  <h2>Third-party services</h2>
  <p>
    Your site may rely on third-party services such as hosting, payment processing, analytics, and
    booking integrations. Your use of those services is subject to their own terms, and we are not
    responsible for their availability or performance.
  </p>

  <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
  <p>
    To the maximum extent permitted by law, Siterra is not liable for any indirect, incidental, or
    consequential damages arising from your use of our services or website. Our total liability for any
    claim is limited to the amount you paid for the services giving rise to the claim.
  </p>

  <h2>Governing law</h2>
  <p>
    These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of Florida, without regard to its conflict of
    law provisions. Any dispute arising from these Terms or our services will be handled in the state
    or federal courts located in Florida, and you consent to that jurisdiction.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to these Terms</h2>
  <p>
    We may update these Terms from time to time. Material changes will be reflected by the "last
    updated" date above. Continued use of our services after changes constitutes acceptance.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about these Terms? Email <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>.
  </p>
</Legal>
